(214, 1, '2016-11-20 18:59:52', '2016-11-20 18:59:52', '<strong>A small story which will make you realize no work is low.</strong>\r\n\r\nThis is the story of a Man who is the evade reader of Hindi books being a Marathi guy published Upanyas not one but many\r\n\r\nSo here we go, deep dive, and check out the story of the man from Maharashtra to New Delhi who published many books in Hindi.\r\n\r\n<strong>MANTRA  </strong>\r\n\r\nUse to sell bidi, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cigarette" target="_blank">cigarettes</a> on Vishnu digamber Marg near ITO new Delhi. from 1968 he uses to sell the things and collected the funds to read and write books as he is very keen to write the books\r\n\r\nJourney started in 1968 after selling things he collected money and buy some good books of Hindi writer like Premchandra studied a lot on Gandhi Ji and Swami Vivekananda Ji after having huge struggle in life he never use to look up back he just again made the story truth of rabbit and tortoise in which tortoise kept on walking on the track and ultimately reaches the goal and defeated the 10 time faster guru rabbit due to his over confidence and came first in the race if we compare this from LAXAMAN RAOs life while selling all the stuff he learned Hindi slowly and gradually from Gulshan Nanda books he took 10 years to publish is first book as a chai seller at the same place in Delhi he wrote first upnyaas on his village friend RAMDAS who died in the river on this single incident he wrote down full upnayaas on it in only Hindi. He published 26 books till now but still he use to sell tea.\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_215" align="alignright" width="300"]<img class="size-medium wp-image-215" src="http://www.maikalaal.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/laxaman-rao-india-shakespear-300x225.jpg" alt="Laxman Rao indias shake spear wrote twenty six books" width="300" height="225" /> Laxman Rao indias shake spear wrote twenty six books[/caption]\r\n\r\n<strong>CULTURE</strong>-\r\n\r\nHe love selling tea his reader use to come and take a cup of writers tea and took his upnyaaas and start reading so, he also grown on the internet his books cost only 300 rs he also uses to sell books in e-books format he does not believe in somebody will come and praise him and gift him with the prize.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>ACHIEVEMENTS</strong>-\r\n\r\nTwenty-six books published till now he is having 10000 plus reader who use to read his book. And he also uses to sell tea at the same place he gave his entire life in reading the writing and selling tea now days he is the very popular writer and many news channels took his interview on his writing skills and why he uses to sell tea while being the excellent writer.\r\n\r\nHe always uses to say no work is hard or tough he just says stuck to your roots and follows your dreams just kill all those things which make you distract from your life.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>EARLY LIFE</strong>-\r\n\r\nBorn at AMARAVATI in Maharashtra a initially work as a worker in small company of electricity company and because of some incident that company shuts down now, Laxman Ji has no option he took back step and returned back to the home now villagers use accuses him by saying people use to go from village to city and this guy is coming back from. So anyhow he took 40 rupees from father and went to Bhopal and work as a majdoor in hotel and many other places and finally came down to Delhi and started selling bidi cigarette near ITO many times thrown away from the publishers but he is very ziddi and started collecting money and finally his dream came true in 1979 when he published RAMDAS and got exposer in Writer.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>So, no work is </strong>bakwaas<strong> only it''s up to you what you make from your work.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Never accuse your life always learn something from your life.</strong>', 'India ke writer Laal - Laxman Rao', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'india-ke-writer-laal', '', '', '2016-11-20 20:25:25', '2016-11-20 20:25:25', '', 0, 'http://www.maikalaal.com/?p=214', 0, 'post', '', 0),
