(280, 1, '2016-11-28 10:20:32', '2016-11-28 10:20:32', '&nbsp;\r\n<h2>About India''s SuperComputers</h2>\r\nNow, It''s been a while till now India launched 13 PARAM including PARAM ISHA. The Ignition of supercomputer was born when <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rajiv_Gandhi" target="_blank">Rajiv Gandhi</a> Ex- Prime minister of India begged up in front of USA and Russia to give their Super Computer Technology to India, when Rajiv Gandhi Came back to India he just cried in the meeting, which is conducted by the high profile ministers of the great nation across the world So, After getting disgraced from some big personalities across the world such as USA and Russia.India decided to make their own Super computer, which was named after PARAM and it was initially created by IIT and<a href="http://cdac.in/" target="_blank"> CDAC (Centre for Development of Advanced Computing)</a> the best proud technology diamond institutions in India.\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_282" align="alignright" width="300"]<img class="size-medium wp-image-282" src="http://www.maikalaal.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/maikalaal.com_-300x201.jpg" alt="Dr-Vijay developed something beautiful" width="300" height="201" /> Dr-Vijay developed something beautiful[/caption]\r\n<h2>About PARAM 8000</h2>\r\nIt was created in 1991 to perform multi operation at a single time,it uses 64 CPU to make it faster at that time PARAM used INMOS T800 it is the name of the processor, it was developed by Ann Barron, <strong>Richard Petritz</strong>, and Paul Schroeder on July 1978 in Bristol, UK and processor used Transputers, which were very classic technologies at that time and also fastest at that time It was a distributed memory <strong>MIMD</strong> architecture with a reconfigurable interconnection network. After successful execution of PARAM it was distributed in Germany, UK and Russia &amp; was an amazing work from <strong>IIT Kanpur</strong> guys, its the only place to develop first Supercomputer, which shows first great step in technology from India india make its first mark in the emerging heights of computation.\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n<h1>PARAM 8600</h1>\r\nThe enhance version of PARAM 8000 was embedded with 256 CPU PARAM 8600 &amp; SUPERSPARC II processor to make it faster than PARAM 8000 you can imagine how fast it is from PARAM 8000 when a CPU cycle from 64 to 256 moved. Fairly faster than earlier than PARAM 8000\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_283" align="aligncenter" width="550"]<img class="size-full wp-image-283" src="http://www.maikalaal.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/param-india-supercomputer.jpg" alt="Indian Supercomputer" width="550" height="408" /> Indian Supercomputer[/caption]\r\n<h2>About PARAM 9900</h2>\r\nAnother enhance version of 8600 to perform more activities at the same time with no wasting time to do multiple things at a single time by using massively parallel MPP its stand for using many processors to make execution time of task to very fast or tending towards zero.\r\n<h2>Ignition to Super Computer</h2>\r\nIt was decided when USA denies to give super computer to India by saying India will use Super computer not for agriculture but aslo for developing Missiles and other things or if India found guilty all the things will be banned to India so, this is how our technology experts decided to built his own super computer in India. You know the fact of super Computer was developed by Vijay P. Bhatkar and his team Vijay P. Bhatkar decided to make super computer in India 1987 and by 1991 they launched their first super computer, As we know all the government work is full of laziness its like a old hindi movie it is sure you will be sleeping in between, while watching the movie but, Vijay sir decided to complete it any how in certain period of time. He faced many problem to get started with it in first 6 months he was not able to engage single engineer to work on with PARAM project to make profound PARAM super computer they work continuously for next 3 years non stop and created first super computer for India which makes India very proud.\r\n<h2>Profile of <a href="https://www.google.co.in/url?sa=t&amp;rct=j&amp;q=&amp;esrc=s&amp;source=web&amp;cd=1&amp;cad=rja&amp;uact=8&amp;ved=0ahUKEwio4J6ilMvQAhVJjpQKHQtyAd0QFggcMAA&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FVijay_P._Bhatkar&amp;usg=AFQjCNHSwEflSo741eoWNldSWPetDTqsTA" target="_blank">Vijay P. Bhatkar</a></h2>\r\nIIT Delhi Alumnus awarded with Padambhusan he is the guy behind PARAM super Computer.\r\n\r\n <em>Padma Bhushan (2015)</em>\r\n<em>  Ramanuja Trust Award (2007)</em>\r\n<em>  FICCI Award (1983)</em>\r\n<em>  Petersburg Prize (2004)</em>\r\n<em>  Padma Shri (2000)</em>\r\n<em>  Priyadarshni Award (2000)</em>\r\n<em>  National Research Development Corporation (NRDC) Award (198485</em>\r\n<em>  Gold Medal Award of Indian Geo-technical Society (1976</em>\r\n<em>  Electronics Man of the Year (1992)</em>\r\n<h2>Something More</h2>\r\nNow India is having one of the most advance super computer, it was displayed abroad and gain popularity Maikalaal want to bring all the great India Magician or Creatorr or Scientist whatever you say, but cannot neglect the natural fact that they are  Mai ka laal and I am proud of them by writing this and solemnly sware to work as great our scientist did.\r\n\r\nSo, now here is the description of something about latest supercomputer, it is PARAM ISHA, which is one of the great Super computers, but, before reading about the making of the Supercomputer be must first understand in which field Supercomputer are used and how they used in todays world to solve some big or complex problem around the world and make people life easy by giving them an early prediction of the weather and danger which are coming along on their way.\r\nHere is the list which will make you learn how vital this creation is -\r\n In weather forecasting\r\n Aerodynamic research\r\n Probabilistic analysis\r\n Radiation shielding modelling\r\n Brute force code breaking\r\n 3D test simulation as a substitute for legal conduct Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty\r\n Molecular Dynamic Simulation.\r\n\r\nAbove mentioned field''s have grown with this innovation.\r\n<h2>Lets learn about Latest PARAM</h2>\r\nPARAM ISHAN (Name of Lord Shiva) is crafted by IITG and CDAC &amp; it has the memory of 300 TB (Terabyte) and having 250 Flip Flops,which use to solve major equation problem altogether &amp; keeps our defense system ahead in the horse race of participating countries.\r\nLots of creative &amp; academic brains are behind this innovative discovery, but the architecture of the Super computer was same.\r\nForthcoming Super Computer in 2017 PARAM Kanchenjunga.\r\n"INDIAN SUPERCOMPUTERS ARE JUST LIKE SOMEONE WHO IS NOT SMART BY LOOKS BUT IF YOU LOOK INSIDE IT YOU WILL LOVE IT"\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="https://goo.gl/8fQXks" target="_blank">Like us on facebook</a>', 'Supercomputer in India', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'supercomputer-in-india', '', '', '2016-11-28 10:24:13', '2016-11-28 10:24:13', '', 0, 'http://www.maikalaal.com/?p=280', 0, 'post', '', 0);
